Privacy Policy
Privacy Policy
Introduction
We understand that your privacy is of great importance to you. Therefore, we (hereinafter referred to as the "Company" or "we") hereby formulate this Privacy Policy (hereinafter referred to as the "Policy") to explain to you how we collect, use, store, share and protect the personal information you provide when using our "ToDo Countdown: Widget & Timer" APP (hereinafter referred to as the "App" or "Service"). Please read this Policy carefully before using our App so that you can understand how we handle your personal information.
1. Collection of Information
Registration Information: When you register as our user, we may ask you to provide some basic information, such as username, password, email address, etc. This information is used to verify your identity and help you use our services.
Usage Information: During your use of our App, we may collect data about how you use the App, such as event creation, editing, deletion records, and App crash reports. This data helps us improve the quality of our services and optimize the user experience.
Device Information: In order to provide better services, we may collect your device information, including device model, operating system version, IP address, etc. This information is used for statistical analysis to understand user distribution and device compatibility.
Third-party services: If you choose to log in or share content to a third-party platform through a social media account, we will obtain your public information, such as nickname, avatar, etc., from the relevant platform based on your authorization.
2. If you have any questions, complaints or suggestions about our privacy policy or information processing methods, please contact us through the following methods:
Email: zfly3454@gmail.com
We promise to respond and handle your feedback as soon as possible after receiving it.
3. Use of information
Provide services: We use the collected information to provide and improve our services to you, including but not limited to event reminders, data analysis, user support, etc.
Personalized experience: We may provide you with more personalized content and recommendations based on your usage habits and behavioral data.
Security and compliance: We may use your information to ensure account security, prevent fraud, and comply with relevant laws and regulations.
4. Storage and protection of information
Security measures: We take reasonable physical, electronic and management measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, use, disclosure, tampering or destruction.
Data storage: Your personal information may be stored on our or our service providers' servers, which may be located in different countries and regions. We ensure that all data is processed in accordance with this policy and local laws and regulations.
Data retention: We only retain personal information necessary to achieve the purposes described in this policy and delete or anonymize it when it is no longer needed.
5. Sharing and disclosure of information
Third-party services: We may work with third-party service providers to support our services, such as server hosting, data analysis, etc. We will sign confidentiality agreements with these providers and require them to process your personal information in accordance with this policy and our instructions.
Legal requirements: We may disclose your personal information when required by laws and regulations or when requested by government agencies or judicial authorities.
Mergers and acquisitions: In the case of corporate mergers, acquisitions or asset transfers, we may transfer your personal information to a new owner or controller, but we will require the new recipient to continue to comply with this policy.
6. Your rights
Access and correction: You have the right to access and correct your personal information held by us.
Deletion: You have the right to request us to delete your personal information in compliance with legal provisions.
Rejection or withdrawal of consent: You have the right to refuse us to collect your personal information or withdraw your consent after providing it. But please note that this may affect your use of our services.
Complaints and Suggestions: If you have any questions, complaints or suggestions about our privacy policy or information processing methods, please contact us through our contact information.
7. Policy Changes
We reserve the right to modify this policy at any time. Any changes will be notified to you in the application or through other appropriate means. Please check this policy regularly to understand the latest privacy protection measures.
8. User Consent for Data Processing Related to Refund Requests
In accordance with the App Store’s refund policy, when a user initiates a refund request, our server will receive a notification (CONSUMPTION_REQUEST) from Apple. In such cases, we will provide Apple with data related to the user’s subscription to assist Apple in making a decision regarding the refund request. Please note that the data provided is strictly limited to subscription-related consumption information and does not include any personal or sensitive data. We are committed to complying with Apple’s requirements and ensuring that all data processing activities fully adhere to privacy protection laws and regulations. By using this app, you consent to the transmission of your subscription consumption data to Apple, as required for processing refund requests, in compliance with the App Store’s refund policies.
